House Resolution 265
By: Representative Powell of the 33rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Gary Minyard, recipient of the 2024 Pioneers in Education Award; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Gary Minyard, a retired agriculture teacher and dedicated Franklin County
4 Board of Education member, has been honored as a recipient of the 2024 Pioneers in
5 Education Award in recognition of his exceptional contributions and years of service; and
6 WHEREAS, a native of Franklin County, he earned his associate's degree from Emmanuel
7 College and obtained his bachelor's, master's, and specialist degrees from the University of
8 Georgia, establishing a strong foundation for his lifelong career in education; and
9 WHEREAS, after teaching for a year in Wilkes County, he returned to Franklin County and
10 dedicated 39 years of exemplary service to the Franklin County School System, instructing
11 at both the middle and high school levels and retiring in 2014; and
12 WHEREAS, he played a pivotal role in developing one of the most successful agricultural
13 programs in the State of Georgia, leading the Franklin County FFA Chapter to state and
14 national recognition as well as advising numerous state officers and national winners; and
