15 WHEREAS, his leadership extended beyond the classroom through his service with the
16 Georgia Vocational Association, earning him the National Association of Agricultural
17 Educators Lifetime Achievement Award in recognition of his lasting impact on agricultural
18 education; and
19 WHEREAS, in addition to his service on the Franklin County Board of Education, he is an
20 active member of the Hart EMC Foundation Board, Gideons International, and Zidon Baptist
21 Church, where he serves as a deacon; and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this outstanding individual be
23 appropriately honored during this special time.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body commend Gary Minyard, recipient of the 2024 Pioneers in
26 Education Award, for his remarkable contributions to education, his lifelong dedication to
27 agriculture, and his continued service to the Franklin County community as well as extend
28 best wishes for future health and happiness.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Gary
31 Minyard.
